  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Adventurer's Armory 2 pg. 9</em>, <em>Gnomes of Golarion pg. 22</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 30 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 12 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 (small), 1d10 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> reach, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Polearms</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>The blade of this glaive is serrated and mounted on an axle, around which a heavy cord is wrapped. When the cord is pulled as a move action, the blade spins rapidly for a number of rounds equal to your Strength bonus. While the blade is spinning, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the weapon. When the blade is not spinning, treat this weapon as a glaive.</p>"
